cIpInLenErrors.name: cIpInLenErrors
cIpInLenErrors.description: Number of packets received with an inconsistant Header/Packet length

cIpInVersionErrors.name: cIpInVersionErrors
cIpInVersionErrors.description: Number of packets received with an incorrect IP version number.

cIpInCSErrors.name: cIpInCSErrors
cIpInCSErrors.description: Number of packets received with an incorrect IP checksum.

cIpTTLZero.name: cIpTTLZero
cIpTTLZero.description: Number of packets that would have been forwarded but their TTL went to 0.

cIpReasmTimeOuts.name: cIpReasmTimeOuts
cIpReasmTimeOuts.description: Number of reassmebly timeouts. This is included inthe ipReasmFails object.

cIpNetToMediaTableSize.name: cIpNetToMediaTableSize
cIpNetToMediaTableSize.description: The maximum number of entries that can be in the cIpNetToMediaTable/ipNetToMediaTable.

cIpNetToMediaCompleteTimeOut.name: cIpNetToMediaCompleteTimeOut
cIpNetToMediaCompleteTimeOut.description: The maximum age, in minutes, that a completed entry may remain in the table before it is timed out and discarded.

cIpNetToMediaInCompleteTimeOut.name: cIpNetToMediaInCompleteTimeOut
cIpNetToMediaInCompleteTimeOut.description: The maximum age, in minutes, that an incomplete entry may remain in the table before it is timed out and discarded.

cIpNetToMediaIns.name: cIpNetToMediaIns
cIpNetToMediaIns.description: Total number of arp packets received.

cIpNetToMediaInLenErrs.name: cIpNetToMediaInLenErrs
cIpNetToMediaInLenErrs.description: Total number of arp packets received which had inconsistant or incorrect lengths. These packets are ignored.

cIpNetToMediaInNotEther.name: cIpNetToMediaInNotEther
cIpNetToMediaInNotEther.description: Total number of arp packets received which specified a hardware type other than Ethernet. These packets are ignored.

cIpNetToMediaInNoArpOnIf.name: cIpNetToMediaInNoArpOnIf
cIpNetToMediaInNoArpOnIf.description: Number of ARP packets received in an interface for which ARP is disabled.

cIpNetToMediaInIp.name: cIpNetToMediaInIp
cIpNetToMediaInIp.description: Number of ARP packets received specifying IP.

cIpNetToMediaInIpTrailers.name: cIpNetToMediaInIpTrailers
cIpNetToMediaInIpTrailers.description: Number of ARP packets received specifying IP Trailers.

cIpNetToMediaInUnkProtos.name: cIpNetToMediaInUnkProtos
cIpNetToMediaInUnkProtos.description: Number of ARP packets received specifying an unknown protocol.

cIpNetToMediaInSourceBcast.name: cIpNetToMediaInSourceBcast
cIpNetToMediaInSourceBcast.description: Number of ARP packets received with a broadcast or multicast source hardware address.

cIpNetToMediaInDups.name: cIpNetToMediaInDups
cIpNetToMediaInDups.description: Number of ARP packets received that originated from another node but had the IP address of this node in the packet's source protocol address field.

cIpNetToMediaInProxyOks.name: cIpNetToMediaInProxyOks
cIpNetToMediaInProxyOks.description: Number of proxy ARP requests that we received and have answered.

cIpNetToMediaReqBadAddrs.name: cIpNetToMediaReqBadAddrs
cIpNetToMediaReqBadAddrs.description: Number of times that a request was for an incorrect IP address (such as the broadcast).

cIpNetToMediaNoResponses.name: cIpNetToMediaNoResponses
cIpNetToMediaNoResponses.description: Number of times that a request timed out.

cIpNetToMediaAgeOuts.name: cIpNetToMediaAgeOuts
cIpNetToMediaAgeOuts.description: Number of times that an entry was aged out of the arp cache because it had not been referenced recently.

cIpNetToMediaTable.name: cIpNetToMediaTable
cIpNetToMediaTable.description: Table containing Constellation extensions to the IP Address Translation (IpNetToMedia) table defined above.

cIpNetToMediaEntry.name: cIpNetToMediaEntry
cIpNetToMediaEntry.description: Each entry contains Constellation extensions for one IpAddress to `physical' address equivalence.

cIpNetToMediaIfIndex.name: cIpNetToMediaIfIndex
cIpNetToMediaIfIndex.description: The interface on which this entry's equivalence is effective. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

cIpNetToMediaNetAddress.name: cIpNetToMediaNetAddress
cIpNetToMediaNetAddress.description: The IpAddress corresponding to the media- dependent `physical' address.

cIpNetToMediaRefTime.name: cIpNetToMediaRefTime
cIpNetToMediaRefTime.description: The value of sysUpTime when this entry was last referenced.

cIpNetToMediaProxyRespond.name: cIpNetToMediaProxyRespond
cIpNetToMediaProxyRespond.description: Is true(1) if this node willrespond to this IP Address following the rules of proxy arp. Otherwise this object is false(2). Setting this object to false(2) will have the effect of preventing this node from responding to this address. Setting this object to true(1) will cause this node to begin responding to this address.

cIpNetToMediaComplete.name: cIpNetToMediaComplete
cIpNetToMediaComplete.description: Is true(1) if the table entry is complete -- that is to say, the ipNetToMediaPhysAddress contains a valid value. If this object is false then the physical address may not be correct. Typically, a 0 length octet string is returned if the entry is not complete.

cIpNetToMediaUseTrailers.name: cIpNetToMediaUseTrailers
cIpNetToMediaUseTrailers.description: Is true(1) if this entry will use ARP trailers. Otherwise this object is false(2).

cIcmpInRedirectNetTos.description: Number of ICMP Destination Unreachable, Network/TOS Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInRedirectHostTos.name: cIcmpInRedirectHostTos
cIcmpInRedirectHostTos.description: Number of ICMP Destination Unreachable, Host/TOS Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInTimeExcTTL.name: cIcmpInTimeExcTTL

cIcmpInTimeExcReAsm.name: cIcmpInTimeExcReAsm

cIcmpInDestUnNet.name: cIcmpInDestUnNet

cIcmpOutRedirectHost.description: Number of ICMP Destination Unreachable, Host Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutRedirectNetTos.description: Number of ICMP Destination Unreachable, Network/TOS Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutRedirectHostTos.description: Number of ICMP Destination Unreachable, Host/TOS Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutTimeExcTTL.description: Number of ICMP Time Exceeded, TTL Exceeded in Transit messages sent.

cIcmpOutTimeExcReAsm.description: Number of ICMP Time Exceeded, Reassembly Time Exceeded messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnNet.description: Number of ICMP Network Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnHost.name: cIcmpOutDestUnHost
cIcmpOutDestUnHost.description: Number of ICMP Host Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnProtocol.name: cIcmpOutDestUnProtocol
cIcmpOutDestUnProtocol.description: Number of ICMP Protocol Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnPort.name: cIcmpOutDestUnPort
cIcmpOutDestUnPort.description: Number of ICMP Port Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnFragNeeded.name: cIcmpOutDestUnFragNeeded
cIcmpOutDestUnFragNeeded.description: Number of ICMP Fragmentation Needed and DF Set Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnSourceRoute.name: cIcmpOutDestUnSourceRoute
cIcmpOutDestUnSourceRoute.description: Number of ICMP Source Route Failed Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpInLengthErrors.name: cIcmpInLengthErrors
cIcmpInLengthErrors.description: Number of alleged ICMP packets that were not long enough.

cIcmpInChecksumErrors.name: cIcmpInChecksumErrors
cIcmpInChecksumErrors.description: Number of alleged ICMP packets that had a bad checksum.

cIcmpInUnkTypes.name: cIcmpInUnkTypes
cIcmpInUnkTypes.description: Number of Received ICMP packets with an unknown type field value.

cIcmpInDestUnNetUnknown.name: cIcmpInDestUnNetUnknown
cIcmpInDestUnNetUnknown.description: Number of ICMP Destination Network Unknown Destination Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInDestUnHostUnknown.name: cIcmpInDestUnHostUnknown
cIcmpInDestUnHostUnknown.description: Number of ICMP Destination Host Unknown Destination Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInDestUnSrcIsolated.description: Number of ICMP Source Isolated Destination Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInDestUnHostProhib.name: cIcmpInDestUnHostProhib
cIcmpInDestUnHostProhib.description: Number of ICMP Communication with Host Administratively Prohibited Destination Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInDestUnNetProhib.description: Number of ICMP Communication with Net Administratively Prohibited Destination Unreachable messages received.

cIcmpInDestUnHostTos.description: Number of ICMP Host Unreachable with TOS messages received.

cIcmpOutDestUnHostUnknown.description: Number of ICMP Destination Host Unknown Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cIcmpOutDestUnSrcIsolated.description: Number of ICMP Source Isolated Destination Unreachable messages sent.

cUdpHdrDrops.name: cUdpHdrDrops
cUdpHdrDrops.description: Nr of packets dropped because of internal consistancy problems. This counter is a component of the udpInErrors Count.

cUdpBadCheckSum.name: cUdpBadCheckSum
cUdpBadCheckSum.description: Nr of packets dropped because of an incorrect checksum. This counter is a component of the udpInErrors Count.

cUdpBadLength.name: cUdpBadLength
cUdpBadLength.description: Nr of packets dropped because of an incorrect length. This counter is a component of the udpInErrors Count.

cUdpOtherErrors.name: cUdpOtherErrors
cUdpOtherErrors.description: Nr of packets dropped because of some error other than one of the above. This counter is a component of the udpInErrors Count. The most likely cause of these errors is a problem in the internal IPC mechanism. Probably because some process that was supposed to be receiving packets is not.

cUdpNoChecksum.name: cUdpNoChecksum
cUdpNoChecksum.description: Nr of packets received with a checksum of 0. This is not an error condition but indicates that there are mentally retarded hosts on the network.

cSnmpInCommunityMessages.name: cSnmpInCommunityMessages
cSnmpInCommunityMessages.description: Number of messages received that use the community- based authentication scheme.

ifExtnsTable.name: ifExtnsTable
ifExtnsTable.description: A list of interfaces extension entries. The number of entries is given by the value of ifNumber, defined in [4,6].

ifExtnsEntry.name: ifExtnsEntry
ifExtnsEntry.description: An extension to the interfaces entry, defined in [4,6], containing additional objects at the subnetwork layer and below for a particular interface.

ifExtnsIfIndex.name: ifExtnsIfIndex
ifExtnsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the interface for which this entry contains extended management information. The value of this object for a particular interface has the same value as the ifIndex object, defined in [4,6], for the same interface.

ifExtnsChipSet.name: ifExtnsChipSet
ifExtnsChipSet.description: This object identifies the hardware chip set being used in the interface. The assignment of OBJECT IDENTIFIERs to various types of hardware chip sets is defined elsewhere. This document assigns only the value: unknownChipSet for use if the chip set in use is unknown. Note that unknownChipSet is a syntactically valid object identifier, and any conformant implementation of ASN.1 and the BER must be able to generate and recognize this value.

ifExtnsRevWare.name: ifExtnsRevWare
ifExtnsRevWare.description: An arbitrary octet string that describes the firmware version of this interface. It is intended that this should be human readable. It must only contain ASCII printable characters. Typically this will be the firmware version of the main interface software.

ifExtnsMulticastsTransmittedOks.name: ifExtnsMulticastsTransmittedOks
ifExtnsMulticastsTransmittedOks.description: The count of frames successfully transmitted to a subnetwork or link-layer multicast destination address other than a broadcast address. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

ifExtnsBroadcastsTransmittedOks.name: ifExtnsBroadcastsTransmittedOks
ifExtnsBroadcastsTransmittedOks.description: The count of frames successfully transmitted to a subnetwork or link-layer broadcast addresses. It does not include frames sent to a multicast address.

ifExtnsMulticastsReceivedOks.name: ifExtnsMulticastsReceivedOks
ifExtnsMulticastsReceivedOks.description: The count of frames successfully received that are directed to an active subnetwork or link-layer multicast address (for a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses). This does not include frames directed to a broadcast address, nor frames received with errors.

ifExtnsBroadcastsReceivedOks.name: ifExtnsBroadcastsReceivedOks
ifExtnsBroadcastsReceivedOks.description: The count of frames successfully received that are directed to a subnetwork or link-layer broadcast address.

ifExtnsPromiscuous.name: ifExtnsPromiscuous
ifExtnsPromiscuous.description: This object has a value of false(2) if this interface only accepts packets/frames that are addressed to this station. This object has a value of true(1) when the station accepts all packets/frames transmitted on the media. The value true(1) is only legal on certain types of media. If legal, setting this object to a value of true(1) may require the interface to be reset before becoming effective.

ifExtnsRcvAddrTable.name: ifExtnsRcvAddrTable
ifExtnsRcvAddrTable.description: This table contains an entry for each address (broadcast, multicast, or uni-cast) for which the system will receive packets/ frames on a particular interface. When an interface is operating in promiscuous mode, entries are only required for those addresses for which the system would receive frames were it not operating in promiscuous mode.

ifExtnsRcvAddrEntry.name: ifExtnsRcvAddrEntry
ifExtnsRcvAddrEntry.description: A list of objects identifying an address for which the system will accept packets/ frames on a particular interface.

ifExtnsRcvAddrIfIndex.name: ifExtnsRcvAddrIfIndex
ifExtnsRcvAddrIfIndex.description: The value of ifIndex, defined in [4,6], of an interface which recognizes this entry's address.

ifExtnsRcvAddress.name: ifExtnsRcvAddress
ifExtnsRcvAddress.description: An address for which the system will accept packets/frames on this entry's interface.

ifExtnsRcvAddrStatus.name: ifExtnsRcvAddrStatus
ifExtnsRcvAddrStatus.description: This object has the value nonVolatile(4) for those entries in the table which are valid and will not be deleted by the next restart of the managed system. Entries having the value volatile(3) are valid and exist, but have not been saved, so that will not exist after the next restart of the managed system. Entries having the value other(1) are valid and exist but are not classified as to whether they will continue to exist after the next restart. Entries having the value invalid(2) are invalid and do not represent an address for which an interface accepts frames. Setting an object instance to one of the values other(1), volatile(3), or nonVolatile(4) causes the corresponding entry to exist or continue to exist, and to take on the respective status as regards the next restart of the managed system. Setting an object instance to the value invalid(2) causes the corresponding entry to become invalid or cease to exist. It is an implementation-specific matter as to whether the agent removes an invalidated entry from the table. Accordingly, management stations must be prepared to receive tabular information from agents that corresponds to entries not currently in use. Proper interpretation of such entries requires examination of the relevant ifExtnsRcvAddrStatus object instance.

dot3Table.name: dot3Table
dot3Table.description: Status information and control variables for a collection of ethernet-like interfaces attached to a particular system.

dot3Entry.name: dot3Entry
dot3Entry.description: Status information and control variables for a particular interface to an ethernet-like medium.

dot3Index.name: dot3Index
dot3Index.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to an ethernet-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

dot3InitializeMac.name: dot3InitializeMac
dot3InitializeMac.description: The initialization status of the MAC and PLS (Physical Layer Signalling) subsystems for a particular interface. The value initialized(1) signifies that the subsystems for a particular interface have been previously initialized; the value uninitialized(2) signifies that they have not been previously initialized. Each alteration of an instance of this object to either of the values initialized(1) or uninitialized(2) is analogous to an invocation of the initializeMAC action defined in [9] and has the effect of (re-)initializing the MAC and PLS subsystems for the associated interface. In particular, all management counters pertaining to the MAC and PLS subsystems for said interface are reset to zero; the receive and transmit layer management state variables (receiveEnabled and transmitEnabled in [9]) are set to enable reception and transmission of frames; the promiscuous receive function is disabled; and multicast reception is disabled.

dot3MacSubLayerStatus.name: dot3MacSubLayerStatus
dot3MacSubLayerStatus.description: The operational status of the MAC sublayer for a particular interface. The value enabled(1) signifies that the MAC sublayer for said interface is operational for both transmitting and receiving frames -- that is, that the value of both the receive and transmit layer management state variables (receiveEnabled and transmitEnabled in [9]) for said interface are true. The value disabled(2) signifies that the MAC sublayer for said interface is not operational for either transmitting or receiving frames. In particular, the value of an instance of this object is disabled(2) whenever the value of the corresponding instance of the dot3Enabled object is false(2). Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value enabled(1) is analogous to an invocation of the enableMACSublayer action defined in [9] and has the effect of starting normal transmit and receive operations (from the ``idle'' state) on the associated interface. In particular, such an alteration has the effect of resetting the PLS for said interface and of setting the receive and transmit layer management state variables (receiveEnabled and transmitEnabled in [9]) to be true. Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value disabled(2) is analogous to an invocation of the disableMACSublayer action defined in [9] and has the effect of terminating transmit and receive operations on the associated interface. In particular, such an alteration has the effect of setting the receive and transmit layer management state variables (receiveEnabled and transmitEnabled in [9]) to be false. Any transmissions/receptions in progress are completed before operation is terminated.

dot3MulticastReceiveStatus.name: dot3MulticastReceiveStatus
dot3MulticastReceiveStatus.description: The multicast receive status for a particular interface. The value enabled(1) signifies that reception of multicast frames by the MAC sublayer is enabled on said interface. The value disabled(2) signifies that reception of multicast frames by the MAC sublayer is not enabled on said interface. Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value enabled(1) is analogous to an invocation of the enableMulticastReceive action defined in [9] and has the effect of enabling multicast frame reception on the associated interface. Actual reception of multicast frames is only possible on an interface when the values for the associated instances of the dot3MulticastReceiveStatus and dot3MacSubLayerStatus objects are enabled(1) and enabled(1), respectively. Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value disabled(2) is analogous to an invocation of the disableMulticastReceive action defined in [9] and has the effect of inhibiting multicast frame reception on the associated interface.

dot3TxEnabled.name: dot3TxEnabled
dot3TxEnabled.description: The transmit layer management state variable (transmitEnabled as defined in [9]) for a particular interface. The value true(1) signifies that the MAC frame transmission is enabled on said interface. The value false(2) signifies that the MAC frame transmission is inhibited on said interface. In particular, the value of an instance of this object is false(2) whenever the value of the corresponding instance of the dot3MacSubLayerStatus object is disabled(2). Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value true(1) is analogous to an invocation of the enableTransmit action defined in [9] and has the effect of enabling MAC sublayer frame transmission on the associated interface. In particular, such an alteration has the effect of setting the transmit layer management state variable (transmitEnabled in [9]) for said interface to be true. Each alteration of an instance of this object to the value false(2) is analogous to an invocation of the disableTransmit action defined in [9] and has the effect of inhibiting MAC sublayer frame transmission on the associated interface. In particular, such an alteration has the effect of setting the transmit layer management state variable (transmitEnabled in [9]) for said interface to be false. Any transmissions in progress are completed before transmission is inhibited.

dot3TestTdrValue.name: dot3TestTdrValue
dot3TestTdrValue.description: The number of 10 MHz ticks which elapsed between the beginning of a TDR measurement and the collision which ended it, for the most recently executed TDR test. If no TDR test has been executed, or the last TDR value is not available, this object has the value 0.

dot3StatsTable.name: dot3StatsTable
dot3StatsTable.description: Statistics for a collection of ethernet-like interfaces attached to a particular system.

dot3StatsEntry.name: dot3StatsEntry
dot3StatsEntry.description: Statistics for a particular interface to an ethernet-like medium.

dot3StatsIndex.name: dot3StatsIndex
dot3StatsIndex.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to an ethernet-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

dot3StatsAlignmentErrors.name: dot3StatsAlignmentErrors
dot3StatsAlignmentErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are not an integral number of octets in length and do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the alignmentError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of [9], counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

dot3StatsFCSErrors.name: dot3StatsFCSErrors
dot3StatsFCSErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that are an integral number of octets in length but do not pass the FCS check. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameCheckError status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of [9], counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.name: dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames
dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by exactly one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames object.

dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.name: dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames
dot3StatsMultipleCollisionFrames.description: A count of successfully transmitted frames on a particular interface for which transmission is inhibited by more than one collision. A frame that is counted by an instance of this object is also counted by the corresponding instance of either the ifOutUcastPkts or ifOutNUcastPkts object and is not counted by the corresponding instance of the dot3StatsSingleCollisionFrames object.

dot3StatsSQETestErrors.name: dot3StatsSQETestErrors
dot3StatsSQETestErrors.description: A count of times that the SQE TEST ERROR message is generated by the PLS sublayer for a particular interface. The SQE TEST ERROR message is defined in section 7.2.2.2.4 of [12] and its generation is described in section 7.2.4.6 of the same document.

dot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.name: dot3StatsDeferredTransmissions
dot3StatsDeferredTransmissions.description: A count of frames for which the first transmission attempt on a particular interface is delayed because the medium is busy. The count represented by an instance of this object does not include frames involved in collisions.

dot3StatsLateCollisions.name: dot3StatsLateCollisions
dot3StatsLateCollisions.description: The number of times that a collision is detected on a particular interface later than 512 bit-times into the transmission of a packet. Five hundred and twelve bit-times corresponds to 51.2 microseconds on a 10 Mbit/s system. A (late) collision included in a count represented by an instance of this object is also considered as a (generic) collision for purposes of other collision-related statistics.

dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.name: dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions
dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to excessive collisions.

dot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.name: dot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors
dot3StatsInternalMacTransmitErrors.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer transmit error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsLateCollisions object, the dot3StatsExcessiveCollisions object, the dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors object, or the dot3StatsExcessiveDeferrals object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of transmission errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.name: dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors
dot3StatsCarrierSenseErrors.description: The number of times that the carrier sense condition was lost or never asserted when attempting to transmit a frame on a particular interface. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented at most once per transmission attempt, even if the carrier sense condition fluctuates during a transmission attempt.

dot3StatsExcessiveDeferrals.name: dot3StatsExcessiveDeferrals
dot3StatsExcessiveDeferrals.description: A count of frames for which transmission on a particular interface is deferred for an excessive period of time.

dot3StatsFrameTooLongs.name: dot3StatsFrameTooLongs
dot3StatsFrameTooLongs.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface that exceed the maximum permitted frame size. The count represented by an instance of this object is incremented when the frameTooLong status is returned by the MAC service to the LLC (or other MAC user). Received frames for which multiple error conditions obtain are, according to the conventions of [9], counted exclusively according to the error status presented to the LLC.

dot3StatsInRangeLengthErrors.name: dot3StatsInRangeLengthErrors
dot3StatsInRangeLengthErrors.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface with a length field value that falls between the minimum unpadded LLC data size and the maximum allowed LLC data size inclusive and that does not match the number of LLC data octets received. The count represented by an instance of this object also includes frames for which the length field value is less than the minimum unpadded LLC data size.

dot3StatsOutOfRangeLengthFields.name: dot3StatsOutOfRangeLengthFields
dot3StatsOutOfRangeLengthFields.description: A count of frames received on a particular interface for which the length field value exceeds the maximum allowed LLC data size. The count represented by an instance of this object is not incremented in implementations that observe Ethernet encapsulation conventions (by which the IEEE 802.3 length field is interpreted as the Ethernet Type field).

dot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.name: dot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors
dot3StatsInternalMacReceiveErrors.description: A count of frames for which reception on a particular interface fails due to an internal MAC sublayer receive error. A frame is only counted by an instance of this object if it is not counted by the corresponding instance of either the dot3StatsFrameTooLongs object, the dot3StatsAlignmentErrors object, the dot3StatsFCSErrors object, the dot3StatsInRangeLengthErrors object, or the dot3StatsOutOfRangeLengthFields object. The precise meaning of the count represented by an instance of this object is implementation- specific. In particular, an instance of this object may represent a count of receive errors on a particular interface that are not otherwise counted.

cConstellationInitialBuffers.name: cConstellationInitialBuffers
cConstellationInitialBuffers.description: Initial amount of buffers available at system startup.

cConstallationBufferDataLength.name: cConstallationBufferDataLength
cConstallationBufferDataLength.description: Number of data bytes that can be stored in each buffer.

cConstellationInstructionRam.name: cConstellationInstructionRam
cConstellationInstructionRam.description: Number of bytes of system instruction ram available. This is fast, zero-wait-state RAM.

cConstellationGlobalDataRam.name: cConstellationGlobalDataRam
cConstellationGlobalDataRam.description: Number of bytes of global data ram available. This is RAM contains I/O buffers and other data structures for which zero-wait-state access is not required by the CPU.

cConstellationFastDataRam.name: cConstellationFastDataRam
cConstellationFastDataRam.description: Number of bytes of fast data ram available. This is RAM contains data structures for which the CPU requires zero-wait-state access, such as the bridge forwarding database.

cDot3Table.name: cDot3Table
cDot3Table.description: Extended status information for the Constellation specific LANCE and ILACC drivers.

cDot3Entry.name: cDot3Entry
cDot3Entry.description: Proprietary status information for a particular interface

cDot3Index.name: cDot3Index
cDot3Index.description: An index value that uniquely identifies an interface to an ethernet-like medium. The interface identified by a particular value of this index is the same interface as identified by the same value of ifIndex.

cDot3Disables.name: cDot3Disables
cDot3Disables.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because the interface was disabled

cDot3MauDisconnect.name: cDot3MauDisconnect
cDot3MauDisconnect.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because m_lance_cs_mau_connected was 0.

cDot3Babbles.name: cDot3Babbles
cDot3Babbles.description: Number of times the LANCE/ILACC Babble bit was set.

cDot3MerrDisconnect.name: cDot3MerrDisconnect
cDot3MerrDisconnect.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because the memory error bit was set.

cDot3TxonDisconnect.name: cDot3TxonDisconnect
cDot3TxonDisconnect.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because the txon bit was off.

cDot3RxonDisconnect.name: cDot3RxonDisconnect
cDot3RxonDisconnect.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because the rxon bit was off.

cDot3XmitFailure.name: cDot3XmitFailure
cDot3XmitFailure.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC disconnects that occured because no packets were received and every transmit attempt resulted in a failure.

cDot3XmitBuffErr.name: cDot3XmitBuffErr
cDot3XmitBuffErr.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC transmit buffer errors that occured.

cDot3XmitUflo.name: cDot3XmitUflo
cDot3XmitUflo.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC transmit underflo errors that occured.

cDot3RcvBuffErr.name: cDot3RcvBuffErr
cDot3RcvBuffErr.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC receive buffer errors that occured.

cDot3RcvOflo.name: cDot3RcvOflo
cDot3RcvOflo.description: Number of LANCE/ILLAC receive overflo errors that occured.

cDot3Startless.name: cDot3Startless
cDot3Startless.description: Number of times that the driver did not get a start-of-message when one was expected. This if for reception.

cDot3Endless.name: cDot3Endless
cDot3Endless.description: Number of times that the driver detected the start of one packet without detecting the end of the previous packet. This is for reception.

cLocalTime.name: cLocalTime
cLocalTime.description: This entity is a string in the format hh:mm [am|pm] representing the local time on the device.

cLocalDate.name: cLocalDate
cLocalDate.description: This entity is a string in the format mm/dd/yy or dd-mm-yy representing the local date on the device.

cLocalCtpMode.name: cLocalCtpMode
cLocalCtpMode.description: This entity determines whether the local console is using standard vt100 key mappings or extended key mappings.

cRemoteCtpMode.name: cRemoteCtpMode
cRemoteCtpMode.description: This entity determines whether remotely logged in consoles use standard vt100 key mappings or extended key mappings.

cBridgeStatsAveraging.name: cBridgeStatsAveraging
cBridgeStatsAveraging.description: This entity determines whether the bridge statistics screens use time averaged or absolute values

cBranchTargetCache.name: cBranchTargetCache
cBranchTargetCache.description: This entity determines whether the CPU's branch target cache is enabled or not.

cOperAcctTable.name: cOperAcctTable
cOperAcctTable.description: This table allows an administrator to configure the operar accounts which grant access to the system. There are up to 60 accounts in the system.

cOperAcctEntry.name: cOperAcctEntry
cOperAcctEntry.description: Information on one entry in the operator accounts database.

cOperIndex.name: cOperIndex
cOperIndex.description: This variable indexes the table of operator accounts.

cOperPriv.name: cOperPriv
cOperPriv.description: This variable gives the privileges associated with a particular account. Valid values for the field are: privNone delete account, privOper operator privileges, privAdmin administrator privileges. Administrators are allowed to configure security.

cOperPasswd.name: cOperPasswd
cOperPasswd.description: This is the password assocated with the given account. A get on this variable will return an empty string.

cOperStatus.name: cOperStatus
cOperStatus.description: This is the current status of the row. The only valid values for a manager to set this value to are createRequest(2) or invalid(4). The agent may return any of valid(1), underCreation(3) or invalid(4).

cSnmpCommunityTable.name: cSnmpCommunityTable
cSnmpCommunityTable.description: Constellation proprietary information about configured SNMP communities. Managers can configure communities, but at least one community must be configured via the console for the manager to be able to communicate with the agent in the first place.

cSnmpCommunityEntry.name: cSnmpCommunityEntry
cSnmpCommunityEntry.description: Each entry contains information about the name of a community, the destination to which to send traps, the interface to report on, and the access allowed by this community.

cSnmpCommunityIndex.name: cSnmpCommunityIndex
cSnmpCommunityIndex.description: This variable is a unique index into the snmp community table.

cSnmpCommunity.name: cSnmpCommunity
cSnmpCommunity.description: This variable represents the name of a community which the agent recognizes. Each community must have a unique name.

cSnmpCommunityIf.name: cSnmpCommunityIf
cSnmpCommunityIf.description: This variable associates an interface with the given community. Each community is associated with exactly one interface.

cSnmpCommunityAccess.name: cSnmpCommunityAccess
cSnmpCommunityAccess.description: This variable determines whether the agent using this community may set or only get variables in the MIB.

cSnmpCommunityTrapAddress.name: cSnmpCommunityTrapAddress
cSnmpCommunityTrapAddress.description: This variable represents the address to which the agent will send traps on behalf of the given community.

cSnmpCommunityTrapPort.name: cSnmpCommunityTrapPort
cSnmpCommunityTrapPort.description: This variable represents the port to which the agent will send traps on behalf of the given community.

cSnmpCommunityTrapEnabled.name: cSnmpCommunityTrapEnabled
cSnmpCommunityTrapEnabled.description: This variable determines whether the agent will send traps on behalf of the given community.

cTcpKeepalive.name: cTcpKeepalive
cTcpKeepalive.description: This variable describes, in minutes, how long the TCP waits between keepalive probes.

cTelnetPort.name: cTelnetPort
cTelnetPort.description: This parameter tells the TELNET protocol on which to listen for incoming calls.

cTelnetNegotiate.name: cTelnetNegotiate
cTelnetNegotiate.description: This parameter tells the TELNET protocol whether to negotiate negotiable parameters.

cEtherSWQTable.name: cEtherSWQTable
cEtherSWQTable.description: This table allows contains information about the maximum size and maximum lifetime of each of the packet queues on the LAN ports.

cEtherSWQEntry.name: cEtherSWQEntry
cEtherSWQEntry.description: Each entry contains software queue information for one interface.

cEtherSWQIndex.name: cEtherSWQIndex
cEtherSWQIndex.description: This index is the number of one of the ethernet interfaces. The port names are mapped to integers thusly: e1a - e8a are entries 1-8; e1b - e8b are entries 9-16.

cEtherSWQMaxSize.name: cEtherSWQMaxSize
cEtherSWQMaxSize.description: The maximum number of packets that may be in the queue at one time for this interface.

cEtherSWQMaxTtl.name: cEtherSWQMaxTtl
cEtherSWQMaxTtl.description: The maximum time in milliseconds that a packet may remain in the queue for this interface.

cResetNovram.name: cResetNovram
cResetNovram.description: When this entity is set, novram is cleared.

cRestartSystem.name: cRestartSystem
cRestartSystem.description: When this entity is set, the system is restarted.

cFlashIpAddress.name: cFlashIpAddress
cFlashIpAddress.description: IP address of server with flash download file.

cFlashBootFlag.name: cFlashBootFlag
cFlashBootFlag.description: Flag to determine whether or not to load new flash code.

cFlashGatewayIpAddr.name: cFlashGatewayIpAddr
cFlashGatewayIpAddr.description: IP address of nearest gateway. This variable should only be set if the TFTP server is not on the same network as the bridge.

cLoginTable.name: cLoginTable
cLoginTable.description: This table gives a record of recent logins to the system.

cLoginEntry.name: cLoginEntry
cLoginEntry.description: Each entry describes one login to the system, either remote or local.

cLoginIndex.name: cLoginIndex
cLoginIndex.description: This variable indexes the entries in the Login History Table.

cLoginUser.name: cLoginUser
cLoginUser.description: This variable contains the login name of the user for the current row in the table.

cLoginLocal.name: cLoginLocal
cLoginLocal.description: This variable describes whether the entry specified in this row of the table represents a login from the local console (yes(1)) or remotely (no(2)).

cLoginRemote.name: cLoginRemote
cLoginRemote.description: This entry gives the remote IP address of a remote login.

cLoginFails.name: cLoginFails
cLoginFails.description: This variable returns the number of attempted logins which have failed.

cNodeByAddressTable.name: cNodeByAddressTable
cNodeByAddressTable.description: This Table allows the manager to map MAC addresses to hash buckets and ports in the router.

cNodeByAddressEntry.name: cNodeByAddressEntry
cNodeByAddressEntry.description: Each entry contains the entry for one MAC address.

cNodeByAddressAddr.name: cNodeByAddressAddr
cNodeByAddressAddr.description: This variable is the MAC address for which the manager wishes to find the hash bucket and port.

cNodeByAddressBridge.name: cNodeByAddressBridge
cNodeByAddressBridge.description: This variable is the bridge on which the given MAC address is reached.

cNodeByAddressPort.name: cNodeByAddressPort
cNodeByAddressPort.description: This variable is the port through which the given MAC address is reached.

cNodeByAddressStatus.name: cNodeByAddressStatus
cNodeByAddressStatus.description: This variable gives the status of the given MAC address. If the status is 'permanent,' the contents of cNodeByAddressPort have no meaning.

cNodeByHashTable.name: cNodeByHashTable
cNodeByHashTable.description: This table may be used by the manager to read the contents of the node table, in the order in which entries appear in the hash table.

cNodeByHashEntry.name: cNodeByHashEntry
cNodeByHashEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents one mapping of a MAC address to a bridge.

cNodeByHashIndex.name: cNodeByHashIndex
cNodeByHashIndex.description: This variable is an abstract index into the hash table. The first entry in bucket 0 is entry 1, the second entry in bucket 0 is 2, the first entry in bucket 1 is 3, etc.

cNodeByHashBucket.name: cNodeByHashBucket
cNodeByHashBucket.description: This entry describes in which bucket in the hash table the given entry appears.

cNodeByHashAddress.name: cNodeByHashAddress
cNodeByHashAddress.description: This entry describes the MAC address of the given entry.

cNodeByHashBridge.name: cNodeByHashBridge
cNodeByHashBridge.description: This variable is the bridge on which the given MAC address is reached.

cNodeByHashPort.name: cNodeByHashPort
cNodeByHashPort.description: This variable describes the port through which the corresponding cNodeByHashAddress is accessed.

cNodeByHashStatus.name: cNodeByHashStatus
cNodeByHashStatus.description: This variable gives the status of the given MAC address. If the status is 'permanent,' the contents of cNodeByHashPort have no meaning.

cHardwareStatusTable.name: cHardwareStatusTable
cHardwareStatusTable.description: This table provides a brief description of of the contents and status of each hardware slot.

cHardwareStatusEntry.name: cHardwareStatusEntry
cHardwareStatusEntry.description: Each entry in this table provides information about one LAN or WAN hardware slot.

cHardwareStatusIndex.name: cHardwareStatusIndex
cHardwareStatusIndex.description: This variable is the index into the table of values.

cHardwareStatusSlot.name: cHardwareStatusSlot
cHardwareStatusSlot.description: This variable provides the slot number as it would appear on the 'Hardware Configuration' screen of the console interface.

cHardwareStatusContents.name: cHardwareStatusContents
cHardwareStatusContents.description: This variable describes the hardware associated with a given slot.

cHardwareStatusMacAddr.name: cHardwareStatusMacAddr
cHardwareStatusMacAddr.description: This variable contains the MAC address of the hardware in the given slot.

cHardwareStatusSerialNo.name: cHardwareStatusSerialNo
cHardwareStatusSerialNo.description: This variable returns the constellation serial number for the part in the accessed slot.

cHardwareStatusRevision.name: cHardwareStatusRevision
cHardwareStatusRevision.description: This variable describes the revision of the hardware in the accessed slot.

cHardwareStatusStatus.name: cHardwareStatusStatus
cHardwareStatusStatus.description: This variable gives the status of the hardware.

cClearErrorLog.name: cClearErrorLog
cClearErrorLog.description: Setting this variable erases the accumulated error log from NOVRAM. Reading it is meaningless.

cErrorLogTable.name: cErrorLogTable
cErrorLogTable.description: This table contains the text of errors detected. Errors are stored in nonvolatile memory, and hence preserved across reboots of the box.

cErrorLogEntry.name: cErrorLogEntry
cErrorLogEntry.description: Each entry contains the text of one error message.

cErrorLogIndex.name: cErrorLogIndex
cErrorLogIndex.description: This is the index of an error message, with higher indices indicating more recent messages.

cErrorLogMessage.name: cErrorLogMessage
cErrorLogMessage.description: This is the text of an error message.

newRoot.name: newRoot
newRoot.description: The newRoot trap indicates that the sending agent has become the new root of the Spanning Tree; the trap is sent by a bridge soon after its election as the new root, e.g., upon expiration of the Topology Change Timer immediately subsequent to its election.

topologyChange.name: topologyChange
topologyChange.description: A topologyChange trap is sent by a bridge when any of its configured ports transitions from the Learning state to the Forwarding state, or from the Forwarding state to the Blocking state. The trap is not sent if a newRoot trap is sent for the same transition.
